1
00:00:01,120 --> 00:00:02,720
(CLARA BREATHING HEAVILY)

2
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:09,440
CLARA: Doctor! Doctor!

3
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:10,880
DOCTOR: Yes, you're
the very next thing on the list.

4
00:00:12,320 --> 00:00:13,920
Doctor, help me!

5
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:16,720
Clara, I'm under attack
from four and a bit

6
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,560
battle fleets,
in case you think I'm slacking.

7
00:00:20,440 --> 00:00:23,040
Doctor, I think there's
something in my spacesuit.

8
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:24,880
That's... That's possible, actually.

9
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:26,440
You were too long in the spider mines.

10
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:27,760
CLARA: Okay, explain.

11
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:29,200
DOCTOR: It's possibly a love sprite.

12
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:32,080
Sucks your... Sucks your brain out
through your mouth, hence the name.

13
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:34,160
-It's halfway up my leg.
-Don"t worry, it's just hungry.

14
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:35,600
CLARA: Doctor...

15
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:38,480
DOCTOR: Describe the four
most interesting stars you can see.

16
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:40,400
There's a blue one. Quite big.

17
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:41,760
Two little yellowish ones just below.

18
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:43,120
Colour of whisky, smaller one blinking?

19
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:45,360
Yes. It's in the back of my neck.
I can feel it.

20
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:47,680
Great!
So asphyxiation would kill you first.

21
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:49,360
Can you see a nebula?

22
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:51,920
Can you see a nebula
in a sort of wing-shape,

23
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,520
-bit green at the end?
-(EXPLOSIONS)

24
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:55,360
-Yes. Yes, I can.
-Great.

25
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,920
I've seen it, too.
I wonder where it was.

26
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:00,240
Doctor.

27
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:02,880
(SCREAMING) Doctor!

28
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:05,360
(GRUNTING)

29
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:06,480
(CLARA COUGHING)

30
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:09,480
(SQUELCHES)

31
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:11,440
(EXCLAIMS)

32
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:12,720
(COUGHING)

33
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:13,840
(EXHALES)

34
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:15,240
How did we do?

35
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:18,120
Oh! Not a word about
my spot-on materialization skills.

36
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,760
What about all the Philosians?
Are they safe?

37
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:20,920
Huh?

38
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:23,480
Oh, yeah.

39
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:27,120
Well, I lured their attackers
halfway across the universe

40
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,520
and drained their weapons banks.

41
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:31,320
Not to mention,
I also saved a school teacher

42
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,600
from having her brains devoured

43
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,800
and being asphyxiated in deep space.

44
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:36,440
So now, if you don't mind,

45
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:38,720
I'm gonna go outside
and wipe my boot on the grass.

46
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:41,120
(DOOR OPENS)

47
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,840
What's to stop them rearming
and trying again?

48
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,080
Nothing.

49
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:54,480
But the Philosians will be
ready for them this time.

50
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:57,240
It's the best I could do, Clara.

51
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:58,360
I'm not actually the police.

52
00:01:58,440 --> 00:01:59,800
That's just what it says on the box.

53
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:01,720
You are always talking about
what you can and can't do,

54
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:03,560
but you never tell me the rules.

55
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,320
We're time travellers.

56
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:08,080
We tread softly.

57
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:11,000
It's okay to make ripples
but not tidal waves.

58
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:12,640
You are a tidal wave.

59
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,400
Don't say that.

60
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:15,640
(SWORDS WHOOSHING)

61
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,640
CLARA: Doctor.

62
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:28,200
No, no, not Vikings.

63
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,880
-(SWORDS WHOOSHING)
-I'm not in the mood for Vikings.

64
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:33,040
-You're coming with us.
-DOCTOR: No.

65
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,880
I'm not. And you want to know why?

66
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,680
(VIKINGS GROWLING)

67
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:41,920
On my face, right now,
more advanced technology

68
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,560
than your species will manage
over the next nine million years.

69
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,560
-Clara.
-Yeah.

70
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,680
We're going with the Vikings.

71
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:55,480
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

72
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,760
(HORN BLOWING)

73
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,320
(CHEERING)

74
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:15,040
ASHILDR: You're back. All of you.

75
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:16,840
Are all of you back?

76
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:19,520
I'm told so. I haven't counted.

77
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,120
-I'm back.
-(LAUGHS)

78
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,040
I had a dream you'd all died.

79
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:26,000
It was so real
I thought I made it happen.

80
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:30,280
Well, if ever does, I'm sure you'll find
some way to blame yourself.

81
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,600
I wish none of you had to go.

82
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,920
CLARA: Plan, Doctor? Any time soon.

83
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,360
-I do have a plan.
-Yeah, that's what you keep saying.

84
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,160
For two days on a longboat.

85
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,280
Well, only because
you were looking worried.

86
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:42,200
Well, only because you kept saying,
"I do have a plan.”

87
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,680
-I do have a plan.
-There you go.

88
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,040
(INHALES)

89
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:52,560
You all right? Do you know her?

90
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,760
Never seen her before in my life.

91
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:55,960
Okay, so why are you staring?

92
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:58,400
I don't know. Nothing, probably.

93
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:00,320
Too much time travel. It happens.

94
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,520
What happens?

95
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:04,120
People talk about premonition
as if it's something strange.

96
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,400
It's not.

97
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:07,720
It's just remembering
in the wrong direction.

98
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,640
DOCTOR: Okay, plan.

99
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:19,840
We meet the boss-man
and we do the usual.

100
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,320
-Which is?
-Replace him.

101
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,800
-Father.
-CLARA: That one.

102
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:26,600
To the primitive mind,
advanced technology can seem like magic.

103
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,400
It's gonna be the yo-yo again, isn't it?

104
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,760
Yeah.

105
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:31,160
It's in my pocket somewhere.

106
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,400
VIKING: We have travelled far.
We have fought...

107
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,160
How did you do that?

108
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,400
Magic.

109
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,800
...many miracles and much treasure.

110
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:41,320
-(ALL EXCLAIMING)
-How dare you insult our chief?

111
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:45,880
I am very, very cross with you.

112
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,600
I am very disappointed!

113
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:54,840
I have taken human form
to walk among you.

114
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,520
Who are you, old man?

115
00:05:57,040 --> 00:06:01,520
Do you not recognise the sign of Odin?

116
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,920
VIKING: You are not Odin.

117
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:06,320
And that is not Odin's sign.

118
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:08,760
Oh, and you would know that how exactly?
Have you met Odin?

119
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:11,160
Do you know what Odin looks like?

120
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:13,360
(THUNDERCLAP)

121
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,120
ODIN: Oh, my people.

122
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:29,200
I am Odin.

123
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:37,480
And now, your day of reward
has finally dawned.

124
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:40,800
Do not believe this foolish trickery.

125
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,280
It's supposed to do that.

126
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:48,680
Your mightiest warriors
will feast with me tonight

127
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:53,720
in the halls of Valhalla.

128
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:08,120
Stay still.
Stay very, very, still.

129
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,480
CLARA: That's not really Odin, is it?

130
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:10,720
He doesn't even know yo-yo.

131
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,600
(VIKINGS SCREAMING)

132
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,720
CLARA: So, this is an invasion?

133
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:17,360
No, this is a harvest.

134
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,760
The strongest, the fittest...

135
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,360
The weak and the young
they leave behind.

136
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:24,560
(GRUNTS)

137
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:29,680
-We have to help them.
-We have to not get chosen.

138
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:32,160
Clara. Clara!

139
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,840
Have you still got the eye-patch thing?

140
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:34,960
(WHISPERS) Clara...

141
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:39,680
(WHISPERING) Point it at my chains
and think the word "Open."”

142
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:45,880
Say it with your mind.

143
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,200
DOCTOR: Clara!

144
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,160
Clara!

145
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,720
(CHAINS CLINKING)

146
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:07,080
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

147
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,640
MAN: Welcome to Valhalla, my ladies.

148
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,960
(VIKING GRUNTING)

149
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,680
(GRUNTS)

150
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,760
(LAUGHS)

151
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,000
No, wait. Wait!

152
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:43,120
There's nothing to fear, strange men.

153
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,520
We are Odin's chosen.

154
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,480
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

155
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:00,200
(METAL RATTLING)

156
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,200
The wall! It moves!

157
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,520
(MEN SCREAMING INDISTINCTLY)

158
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:11,480
Odin. Odin!

159
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:12,880
Use your blades. Try to jam it.

160
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,680
Come on.

161
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,520
Quick. Pull!

162
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,680
I'm trying!

163
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,240
Quickly!

164
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:39,960
(WHOOSHING)

165
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:53,800
VIKING 1: They took half the village.
VIKING 2: Yeah.

166
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,000
VIKING 2: And it was the good half.

167
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:57,400
They went willingly to Valhalla.

168
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,400
Thus would we all.

169
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:00,600
I wouldn't.

170
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,640
Well, I wouldn't.

171
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,440
I'm not good with heights.

172
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,800
Oh, stop it.

173
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:08,120
All of you stop it right now.

174
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,080
Homo sapiens, you are
an intelligent species.

175
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,840
Stop lying to yourselves.

176
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:15,760
Choose your words carefully, false Odin.

177
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:16,960
Yes, I am a false Odin.

178
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:18,720
That's exactly right. I lied.

179
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:22,040
The big fella in the sky, he lied, too.

180
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,520
You all know it.

181
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:27,200
Because what's the one thing
the gods never do?

182
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:29,360
Gods never actually show up.

183
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,840
Guess what?

184
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:34,680
You got raided.

185
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,640
Guess what else?

186
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,480
I lost someone who matters to me.

187
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,280
So did 1.

188
00:11:19,560 --> 00:11:21,400
Why are we still alive?

189
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,520
ODIN: Because of this.

190
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,240
Explain.

191
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,160
CLARA: I'm sorry.

192
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,400
I didn't mean to make you afraid.

193
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:37,920
I have no reason to fear you.

194
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:40,280
Except you've already analyzed that.

195
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:43,320
And you know it's a technology
from a civilisation

196
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,720
vastly more powerful than your own.

197
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,800
And you will have
also noticed that, um...

198
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,440
I'm wearing a spacesuit.

199
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:52,680
So I'm not from around here.

200
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:55,520
And it's highly unlikely
that I will have come alone.

201
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:56,640
You see, you haven't killed us

202
00:11:57,080 --> 00:12:00,080
because killing us would start a fight
you didn't come here to have.

203
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,240
And you're not sure you could win.

204
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,600
Ooh! Hello.

205
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,120
Time for your medication?

206
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:13,320
Adrenaline testosterone.

207
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:17,640
Extracted from the finest warriors.

208
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:20,960
(GULPING)

209
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,440
(EXHALES)

210
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,840
Nectar!

211
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:31,800
Okay, you must have Vikings
to make warrior juice.

212
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,520
-Nice.
-They what?

213
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,640
CLARA: Why play God?

214
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:37,280
What is a God
but the cattle's name for farmer?

215
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:40,840
What is heaven
but the gilded door of the abattoir?

216
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,600
You're not a farmer.

217
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,320
You're a thief caught in the act.

218
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:46,840
I don't understand. Mashed up?

219
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:48,840
-What are you saying?
-Hush.

220
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:50,160
Go. Now.

221
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,880
Go find Vikings on other planets.

222
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:53,920
The universe is full of testosterone.

223
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,640
Trust me, it's unbearable.

224
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,240
We won't follow you. See?

225
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,400
We don't need to fight.

226
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,240
War is our way.

227
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,520
Ask yourself,
is this a war you really want?

228
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:07,720
ASHILDR: Yes!

229
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,080
You'll pay for what
you have done here today.

230
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:14,680
I am a Viking. Ashildr.

231
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:16,200
Daughter of Ionhar.

232
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:18,080
You have mocked our Gods,

233
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,960
killed our warriors.

234
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,840
And we'll crush you
on the field of battle.

235
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:24,240
-That's better.
-You were about to leave.

236
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,960
You almost had me talking.

237
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,320
Talk is for cowards.

238
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:30,520
-No, no, no. Listen to me.
-I accept your challenge.

239
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,520
-We will crush you.
-Oh, please. Shut up.

240
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,680
Shall we say, this time tomorrow?

241
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:37,640
Ten of my warriors
versus the best of your village.

242
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:39,680
-You will beg for mercy.
-(LAUGHS)

243
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:42,360
I will send you back.

244
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:47,440
You can inform your people
of their impending destruction.

245
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:50,160
-CLARA: Why are you doing this?
-Why else?

246
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:53,000
The joy of war.

247
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:57,120
Can't you see it on my face?

248
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,800
(BEEPS)

249
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:12,920
(GRUNTS)

250
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,880
-Clara.
-My child.

251
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,960
Clara! Clara!

252
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,360
I'm not a hugger.

253
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,640
-Ah. This is...
-Oh! No.

254
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,440
Where are the others?

255
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:34,680
I'm sorry, Father.

256
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,600
I looked them up
at my 2,000 year diary.

257
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,200
-They are called the Mire.
-Okay, Listen.

258
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:40,720
They are one of the deadliest
warrior races in the entire galaxy.

259
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:41,920
-Okay.
-But they are practical.

260
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,120
They get what they want
and then they go.

261
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:45,600
You persuaded them to go, didn't you?
I knew that you would.

262
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:46,840
The deadliest warrior race
in the galaxy?

263
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:48,720
One of them. Yes, why?

264
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:51,640
Because I think this village
just declared war on them.

265
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:57,280
They're coming here tomorrow,
10 of them,

266
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:58,880
to kill everybody in the village.

267
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:02,400
Ashildr, is this true?

268
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,360
It's my fault.

269
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:08,200
Not every misfortune that befalls
this village is down to you.

270
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:11,400
She thinks she brings us bad luck.

271
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:13,160
What bad luck?
You haven't had any bad luck.

272
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:14,240
You're fine.

273
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:16,800
-We're about to be attacked by...
-DOCTOR: Yes, yes, yes, yes.

274
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:19,200
With a whole day to spare.

275
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,920
So, leave.

276
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,600
Hop it. Take off.

277
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,560
Into the woods, split up, hide.

278
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:27,440
Hang about there for a week,
come back home.

279
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:29,840
Make puddings and babies.
That's basically what you do, isn't it?

280
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:32,280
We cannot leave this village.

281
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,080
Yes, you can.

282
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,000
Just pick a direction.

283
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:39,520
Fly like a bird, run like a nose.

284
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:41,400
It's probably a Vikings' saying,
I haven't checked that.

285
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:43,920
No. We will fight.

286
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,760
(VIKINGS AGREEING)

287
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,480
DOCTOR: Really?

288
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:48,840
Well, I don't know if you remember,

289
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:51,560
but they actually took away
all your fighters.

290
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,120
So, uh, what are you?

291
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,680
Farmers, fishermen,

292
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:58,680
web designers. Maybe not that last one.

293
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,360
(WEAPONS CLANKING)

294
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:02,120
We are Vikings!

295
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,280
(ALL CHEERING)

296
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:07,280
Okay. (CLAPS)

297
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:09,920
Tell me this.

298
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:15,080
How many people here
have actually held a sword in battle?

299
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,560
By show of hands.

300
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:23,960
Mmm-hmm. Yeah, baby.

301
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:44,160
The Mire are coming
for each and every one of you.

302
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:45,760
-(SWORD CLANKING)
-So, what're you gonna do?

303
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,680
Raise crops at them?

304
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:49,360
If necessary.

305
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:50,960
I think he was being sarcastic.

306
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:53,520
We're not cowards. We do not run.

307
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:56,280
And a death in battle
is a death with honour.

308
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,360
ALL: Aye.

309
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,880
(BABY CRYING)

310
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,960
DOCTOR: Do babies die with honour?

311
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,760
I am afraid, Mother.

312
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:20,040
Hold me, Mother.

313
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,480
I'm afraid.

314
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:25,560
Um, he speaks baby.

315
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:28,920
DOCTOR: Turn your face
towards me, Mother, for you're...

316
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:31,520
(SCOFFS)

317
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:33,560
You're beautiful...

318
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:35,520
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

319
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,600
And I will sing for you.

320
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:40,600
I'm afraid,

321
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,680
but I will sing.

322
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:47,960
Babies think that laughter is singing,
did you know that?

323
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,720
I applaud your courage,
but I deplore your stupidity.

324
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:56,400
And I will mourn your deaths,
which will be terrifying,

325
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:01,040
painful and without honour.

326
00:18:08,280 --> 00:18:09,440
Stay.

327
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,920
You could help us. I know you could.

328
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,800
I told you to run.

329
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:16,400
That's all the help you need.

330
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,920
That's all the help you're getting.

331
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:37,520
The Earth is safe,
humanity is not in danger.

332
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,080
It's just one village.

333
00:18:42,520 --> 00:18:43,720
Just one village?

334
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:46,280
Suppose I saved it, by some miracle,

335
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:48,240
no TARDIS, no sonic...

336
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:51,720
Just one village defeats the Mire.

337
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,600
What then?

338
00:18:55,080 --> 00:18:57,000
Word gets around,

339
00:18:57,080 --> 00:18:59,400
Earth becomes a target
of strategic value

340
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,400
and the Mire come back.

341
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:04,360
And God knows what else.

342
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:08,120
Ripples into tidal waves,

343
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:10,960
until everybody dies.

344
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:13,400
(BABY CRYING)

345
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,160
-What's it saying?
-She.

346
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:24,680
She's afraid.

347
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,400
Babies sense danger. They have to.

348
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:28,760
Tell me.

349
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:34,880
Mother, I hear thunder.
Mother, I hear shouting.

350
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:37,680
You're my world,
but I hear other worlds now.

351
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:42,840
Beyond the unfolding of your smile...

352
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:47,000
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

353
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,720
...is that other kindness.

354
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:53,800
I'm afraid. Will they be kind?

355
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:55,960
The sky is crying now,

356
00:19:57,840 --> 00:19:59,640
fire in the water,

357
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:04,040
fire in the water.

358
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:14,040
You just decided to stay.

359
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:15,640
(CRYING STOPS)

360
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,800
The baby stopped crying.

361
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:32,680
So, when I say "Move," you move.

362
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:34,920
When I say, "Jump,” you say, "How high?”

363
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:36,680
Unless, of course,
there's a gap of some kind

364
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:38,920
which, of course, means
you jump horizontally.

365
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:40,440
Yes, what is it, Lofty?

366
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,320
Sir, my name's not actually "Lofty."
It's Br...

367
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,640
No, it's not. It's Lofty.

368
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:46,920
I've got too much to think about

369
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,320
without everybody
having their own names.

370
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:50,080
So, it's Lofty.

371
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:52,080
You're Lofty, you're Daphne.

372
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:54,920
You're Noggin the Nog.

373
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,320
Z7Z Top.

374
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:58,040
And you're, uh...

375
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,600
Heidi.

376
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:04,200
So, we'll try that again.

377
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,440
Lofty?

378
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:07,720
-What is it?
-Sorry, sir. It's just...

379
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:09,920
Why aren't we practising
with real swords?

380
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,200
Yes, perhaps, you'd like
to field this one, Limpy.

381
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,480
Because we can't be trusted with them.

382
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:18,280
That's right. Yes.

383
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:20,000
You'll be given your real swords back

384
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,280
when you can prove
that you can wave them around

385
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:24,160
without lopping bits off yourself.

386
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,280
Heidi!

387
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:26,600
Why are your eyes closed?

388
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:29,040
Sorry, sir, just not that good
with the sight of blood.

389
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:33,360
No, of course you're not.

390
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:36,400
Swords against those creatures...

391
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:38,440
That won't work, will it?

392
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:39,920
He's just warming up.

393
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:42,160
He hasn't got a plan, yet,

394
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,360
but he will have.

395
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:47,240
And it'll be spectacular.

396
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:48,880
(DOCTOR WHISTLING)

397
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:54,320
Enough theory.
I'm handing out the real swords.

398
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,520
(LAUGHS)

399
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:01,320
-(HORN BLOWING)
-(PEOPLE BUSTLING)

400
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:03,240
That could have gone better.

401
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:04,800
(EXCLAIMS)

402
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,000
Morning.

403
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,920
What happened?

404
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:10,120
The big bang?

405
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:13,120
Dinosaurs, bipeds,
a mounting sense of futility.

406
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:16,960
More recently,
Chuckles hit Lofty over the head,

407
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,760
on his helmet with a sword,

408
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,320
which knocked him out,
there was a little blood,

409
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:23,120
which you saw, and did that.

410
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:25,600
Only the first time, you did it,

411
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:27,840
you knocked a torch into some hay,
which spooked a horse

412
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:31,760
who kicked open the gate, and I'm sure
that you can fill in the rest.

413
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:51,080
(THUNDERCLAP)

414
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:56,120
Weird sounding thunder.

415
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,880
That's not thunder.

416
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:02,240
It's the weapon forges of the Mire,

417
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,720
making sure we hear them.

418
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:07,640
-Well?
-Well...

419
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:10,880
Heidi faints at the mention of blood,
not just the sight any more.

420
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:12,360
He's actually upgraded his phobia.

421
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:13,800
Chuckles...

422
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:16,440
He questions every single order
you give him,

423
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,640
which is gonna be a little...

424
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:18,760
A little bit difficult,

425
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:19,960
a little bit tricky
in the heat of battle.

426
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:22,720
I keep waiting to hear
what your real plan is.

427
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:25,600
Teaching them to fight,
that's the only plan I've got.

428
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:27,720
Turning them into fighters?
That's not like you.

429
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:30,680
-Yeah, I used to believe that, too.
-(LAUGHS)

430
00:23:30,760 --> 00:23:31,960
-What happened?
-You.

431
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:35,320
Oh, Clara Oswald.

432
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:38,440
What have I made of you?

433
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:41,240
It doesn't matter
how well you train them,

434
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:42,360
it's not gonna make a difference.

435
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:44,040
They'll die fighting, with honour.

436
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:45,880
To a Viking,
that's all the difference in the world.

437
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:48,480
A good death?
Is that the best they can hope for?

438
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:50,840
A good death is the best
anyone can hope for,

439
00:23:51,280 --> 00:23:53,080
unless you happen to be immortal.

440
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,880
-Sorry.
-CLARA: No problem.

441
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:00,640
DOCTOR: Good night.
CLARA: You've made an impact there.

442
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:02,240
-Stop it.
-What, she's nice.

443
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:04,360
-I'll fight you for her.
-The human race.

444
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:05,960
You're obsessed.

445
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:09,040
-You all need to get a hobby.
-I've got a hobby. Thanks.

446
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,280
It's you, by the way.

447
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:13,160
Well, get a new one.

448
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:16,640
-Not this.
-Tomorrow it's gonna be a bloodbath.

449
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:17,760
Don't even ask.

450
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:20,000
These people all died hundreds of years
before you were even born.

451
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:21,120
-I'm not running.
-I have a duty of care.

452
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:22,880
No, you don't
because I've never asked for that.

453
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,000
Every time we do something like this,

454
00:24:24,080 --> 00:24:25,880
I keep thinking,
"What if something happens to you?”

455
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:27,000
Well, stop thinking about me.

456
00:24:27,080 --> 00:24:29,080
And start thinking about them,
because you're missing something.

457
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:30,480
-What?
-How're you gonna win?

458
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:33,400
You always miss it,
right up until the last minute.

459
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:36,080
So, put down your sword,
stop playing soldier, and

460
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:37,360
look for it.

461
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,920
Start winning, Doctor.

462
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:41,600
It's what you're good at.

463
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:45,200
ASHILDR: So,
we meet again, fake Odin.

464
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:48,000
Valhalla burns around you.

465
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:50,200
Your army is destroyed.

466
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:55,000
-And now, it is time for you to die!
-(CLEARS THROAT)

467
00:24:57,080 --> 00:24:59,080
-How long have you been there?
-Is that for a puppet?

468
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:00,200
Oh, I love puppets.

469
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:03,200
I make puppets sometimes when I'm...

470
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:04,320
Frightened.

471
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:08,760
When the raiding parties go out,
I make up stories about their battles.

472
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:10,840
Because if you make up the right story,

473
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:13,320
you think it will keep them safe
and they'll all come home.

474
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:15,720
That's okay.

475
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:18,120
You're not the first person
to ever have done that.

476
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:22,480
-Why are you here?
-I'm looking for something I'm missing.

477
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:28,840
What do you think
our chances are tomorrow?

478
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:34,960
We'll be cut down like corn.

479
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:40,080
By this time tomorrow,
every single one of us will be dead.

480
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,280
Yeah.

481
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,280
(SIGHS)

482
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:53,880
-You could go.
-There's nowhere for me except here.

483
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:56,080
This is my place.

484
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:00,760
The sky, the hills, the sea,
the people...

485
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:04,360
Is there nowhere like that for you?

486
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:06,920
Oh, I like a nice view
as much as anyone.

487
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,920
-But...
-Can't wait for the next one.

488
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:12,200
I pity you.

489
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:13,560
I will mourn for you.

490
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:16,600
I know which I'd prefer.

491
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:19,040
You think they are all idiots,
don't you?

492
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:20,360
What, you mean,
the rest of the universe?

493
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:22,120
Um, basically, yes, I do.

494
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:24,280
But they're kind and brave and strong.

495
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:26,120
-And I love them.
-Good.

496
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:27,960
Good, but that won't save you.

497
00:26:28,040 --> 00:26:29,880
I've always been different.

498
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:32,440
All my life, I've known that.

499
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:35,760
The girls all thought I was a boy.

500
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:38,600
The boys all said I was just a girl.

501
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,360
My head is always full of stories.

502
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:43,560
I know I'm strange.

503
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,800
Everyone knows I'm strange.

504
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:49,880
But here, I'm loved.

505
00:26:50,360 --> 00:26:52,840
You tell me to run to save my life.

506
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:57,160
I tell you that leaving this place
would be death itself.

507
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:06,120
I cannot keep you safe.
I do not have the strength.

508
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:09,080
But I will try to
till the last beat of my heart.

509
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:10,920
(BABY CRYING)

510
00:27:12,680 --> 00:27:15,360
If you seek to mock me in this moment...

511
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:17,240
No. No.

512
00:27:17,320 --> 00:27:19,920
No, you go ahead.
You cry all you like.

513
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:22,520
Speaking of cry, is that...
Is that baby getting closer?

514
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,040
(BABY CRYING)

515
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:26,000
Why is Lofty stealing the baby?

516
00:27:26,640 --> 00:27:27,760
That's his child.

517
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:29,480
Oh.

518
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:31,880
-Where is he taking her?
-ASHILDR: The boathouse.

519
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:34,120
He takes her to the boathouse
when she won't settle.

520
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:35,880
She likes the fish.

521
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:38,320
Why would she?

522
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:43,000
Fire in the water.

523
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:45,160
Fire in the water.

524
00:27:45,840 --> 00:27:47,920
Fire in the water. Fire...

525
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,040
Fire in... Fire in the water.

526
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:52,600
Fire in the water! That's it!

527
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,760
That's it. That's it.
That's what I've been missing.

528
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,120
Clara, I found it!

529
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,640
Clara! Clara!

530
00:27:58,360 --> 00:27:59,600
(BABY CRYING)

531
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:01,880
Lofty! Oh!

532
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:04,160
I had no idea that that was your baby.

533
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:05,280
Hello, baby.

534
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:06,600
I had no idea this was
your junior parent.

535
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:08,280
I'm trying to settle her.
She likes all the fish.

536
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:10,040
Okay, you're shouting. What's happened?

537
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,240
You trapped your finger
in something again?

538
00:28:11,320 --> 00:28:13,280
Chuckles, bedtime is cancelled.
Everybody off the hard stuff.

539
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:14,840
We have a long night's work ahead of us.

540
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:16,800
I'm gonna need a blacksmith.
Who's the blacksmith?

541
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:17,920
I'm the blacksmith.

542
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,680
What? Are you the blacksmith?
And you got a baby, too.

543
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:22,080
-He's been at it hammer and tongs.
-Doctor, explain. What's happening?

544
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:24,320
There's gonna be a war tomorrow.

545
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:26,680
And here's some news, this just in.

546
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:28,160
We're gonna win the hell out of it.

547
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:33,320
-How?
-Ashildr, this is your village,

548
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:36,000
and you will never have to leave it.
I swear.

549
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:37,120
Seriously, how?

550
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:40,440
I told you
that we were basically doomed.

551
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:46,000
Did no one in this two-horn town
think to mention that you had eels?

552
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:51,000
-Eels?
-I give you fire in the water.

553
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,280
Electric eels.

554
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:55,400
Yes. Yes.

555
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:57,760
I know exactly how you feel.

556
00:28:57,840 --> 00:28:58,880
Well, not exactly.

557
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,040
She needs changing.

558
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:06,640
-Plan, then?
-And it is a doozy.

559
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:10,360
We need to pull that silvery stuff
out of Clara's spacesuit.

560
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:13,440
We can use it
to magnify the electrical charge.

561
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:16,240
And stop looking confused, look happy!

562
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:19,000
Winning is all about
looking happier than the other guy.

563
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:23,920
Always walk briskly,
it makes you a moving target.

564
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,600
Uh... Oh, that's for Lofty! Lofty!

565
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,520
And talk with confidence.

566
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:29,840
Even if you are terrified.

567
00:29:29,920 --> 00:29:31,560
Act as if you know their plan,

568
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:33,680
and sometimes,
if you are very lucky,

569
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:35,480
they'll actually tell you it.

570
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:37,320
Ah. This is for Ashildr.

571
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:40,800
Then, we deploy the anvil.

572
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:43,640
Now, at this stage,
getting one of their helmets is key.

573
00:29:43,720 --> 00:29:46,200
We get a helmet
and this is over.

574
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:49,800
Then we can mop up the rest
using Ashildr's monstrosity.

575
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:59,760
That is rubbish.

576
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:01,040
I know.

577
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:05,000
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

578
00:30:23,080 --> 00:30:24,600
(VIKINGS CHEERING)

579
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:31,880
Hey! Hello, hey.

580
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:35,200
I'm the Doctor. It's lovely to meet you
to face to, uh... Convincing hologram.

581
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:37,200
You could always go...
(IMITATES BUZZING) ...and get rid of it.

582
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:39,800
No? No, on second thoughts, don't.
That, that... That suits you.

583
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:41,800
It is time to fight.

584
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:43,760
DOCTOR: No, no, no.
We decided against that.

585
00:30:43,840 --> 00:30:45,160
We thought we'd just have a party!

586
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,400
(ALL CHEERING)

587
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:48,200
ODIN: Let me put it another way.

588
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:50,120
You fight or you die.

589
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:51,720
We are unarmed.

590
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:55,240
There isn't a single weapon
in this room,

591
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:57,560
which I'm sure
your systems are telling you that.

592
00:30:58,720 --> 00:31:02,520
You wouldn't open fire
on unarmed civilians, would you?

593
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:05,120
It wouldn't be the first time.

594
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:08,760
(METAL CLINKING)

595
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:18,920
Chuckles, now!

596
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:21,120
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

597
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:30,160
(SCREAMING)

598
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:33,760
Chuckles, switch!

599
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:36,400
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

600
00:31:50,040 --> 00:31:52,080
-Chuckles, off!
-Oh!

601
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:56,960
Don't move!

602
00:31:58,240 --> 00:31:59,280
Go!

603
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:02,800
CLARA: How's it going?

604
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:04,440
Reversing the polarity
of the neutron flow.

605
00:32:04,520 --> 00:32:05,760
I bet that means something.
It sounds great.

606
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:07,360
Ashildr!

607
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:12,000
-Are you ready?
-I'm scared.

608
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,600
You were born for this.

609
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:16,440
(INHALES)

610
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:19,120
Show them a story
they will never forget.

611
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:20,760
(LASERS FIRING)

612
00:32:28,560 --> 00:32:30,280
(INHALES SHARPLY)

613
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:40,480
(ROARS)

614
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:44,360
(GRUNTING)

615
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:47,040
What is this beast?

616
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,400
(LASER GUN FIRING)

617
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:50,280
It's impossible!

618
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:56,000
MIRE: Withdraw! Withdraw!

619
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:57,600
Stand and fight!

620
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:59,160
(ROARING)

621
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:02,320
Withdraw!

622
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:04,720
DOCTOR: See how they run!

623
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:07,200
Withdraw!

624
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:09,120
Cowards!

625
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:10,520
Withdraw!

626
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:13,120
That enough, Ashildr, story's over.

627
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:15,360
Happy ending.

628
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,200
(ROARING)

629
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:20,840
(TRUMPET BLARING)

630
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,000
(LAUGHING)

631
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,960
(FLOORBOARD CREAKING)

632
00:33:28,720 --> 00:33:31,200
-What trickery is this?
-DOCTOR: Ha!

633
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:33,680
Says the man with a fake face!

634
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:36,760
Well, you see, that's the trouble
with viewing reality through technology.

635
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:38,840
It's all too easy
to feed in a new reality.

636
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:40,360
Have you got it? Great.

637
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:43,000
A story to save a town.

638
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:45,640
And a puppet from a nightmare.

639
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:49,800
You see, you've just seen the world
through the eyes of a storyteller.

640
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:53,800
The mighty armies of the Mire,
brutal, sadistic, undefeated.

641
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:55,120
Even I believed the stories.

642
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:57,440
But after today, no one will again.

643
00:33:57,520 --> 00:34:02,040
An army like yours, it lives or dies
on its reputation, its story.

644
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:05,720
And today, you were sent packing
by a handful of farmers and fishermen.

645
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:07,960
-(LAUGHING)
-Not to mention the whole,

646
00:34:08,040 --> 00:34:10,800
wetting your pants and running away
from a puppet debacle...

647
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,720
(LAUGHING) See,
that was really funny.

648
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:14,960
That was hilarious.

649
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:17,360
It's just lucky
that nobody recorded that.

650
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,880
-Wait a minute, we did.
-(RECORDER BEEPS)

651
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:22,240
Cowards/!

652
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,800
You see, all it needed
was the Benny Hilltheme.

653
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:26,000
-The Benny Hilltheme, yes.
-(LAUGHS)

654
00:34:26,080 --> 00:34:29,600
Now you see, we could just keep this
as a funny little film,

655
00:34:29,680 --> 00:34:32,440
and play it every year
at the Christmas party or,

656
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:36,400
I could upload it to the galactic hub
and get a second opinion.

657
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:38,200
So the question you need
to ask yourself is this.

658
00:34:38,720 --> 00:34:41,800
Just how important is
your reputation to you?

659
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:44,920
Here's a little sneak preview,
piped straight into your helmets,

660
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:46,040
free of charge.

661
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:47,240
(RECORDER BEEPS)

662
00:34:48,240 --> 00:34:49,960
-(BENNY HILL THEME PLAYING)
-Ah, wait.

663
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:53,600
-Cowards...
-(LASERS FIRING)

664
00:34:55,040 --> 00:34:57,000
-DOCTOR: If you don't leave right now...
-(RECORDER BEEPS)

665
00:34:57,080 --> 00:35:01,280
...I'll put it out there for all to see
and no one will fear you again.

666
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:06,240
This humiliation will not go unpunished.

667
00:35:06,920 --> 00:35:09,000
We will meet again.

668
00:35:10,160 --> 00:35:12,520
Oh, I hacked your teleporter, sorry.

669
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:14,280
(VIKINGS CHEERING)

670
00:35:15,720 --> 00:35:16,760
(LAUGHS)

671
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:41,560
You did it, Ashildr.

672
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:42,920
You did it.

673
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:44,360
You saved us all!

674
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:45,680
Ashildr?

675
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:50,480
Ashildr?

676
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,080
Ashildr?

677
00:35:53,160 --> 00:35:55,320
Get the helmet off her. Get it off now.

678
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:56,520
(GRUNTING)

679
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:00,840
Ashildr...

680
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:09,000
No pulse.

681
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:11,080
I think...

682
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,440
Doctor, is she dead?

683
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:20,200
(ALL GASPING)

684
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:24,280
I'm sorry.

685
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,560
(WHIMPERING)

686
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:33,800
I'm really, terribly sorry.

687
00:36:55,560 --> 00:36:58,480
-Heart failure, yeah?
-Yeah.

688
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,560
I plugged her into the machine.

689
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:08,200
Used her up like a battery.

690
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,360
(SIGHS)

691
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:16,480
I'm so sick of losing.

692
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,880
You didn't lose.

693
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:22,760
You saved the town.

694
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:27,760
I don't mean the war.

695
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:31,640
I'll lose any war you like.

696
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,960
I'm sick of losing people.

697
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:47,440
Look at you with your eyes,
you're never giving up to anger,

698
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:50,080
and your kindness.

699
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:55,560
One day, the memory
of that will hurt so much

700
00:37:55,640 --> 00:37:57,720
that I won't be able to breathe,
and I will do what I always do,

701
00:37:57,800 --> 00:38:01,160
I'll get in my box
and I'll run and I'lW run...

702
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:06,240
In case all the pain ever catches up,
and every place I go, it will be there.

703
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:07,640
You did your best.

704
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:11,120
She died. There's nothing you can do.

705
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:13,800
I can do anything.

706
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:17,240
There's nothing I can't do.

707
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:18,480
Nothing.

708
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:21,560
But I'm not supposed to.

709
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:25,480
Ripples, tidal waves, rules.

710
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:27,720
I'm not supposed to.

711
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,480
Oh.

712
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:40,320
(EXCLAIMS)

713
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:44,680
What? What's wrong?

714
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:46,120
My face...

715
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:49,520
Who frowned me this face?

716
00:38:50,440 --> 00:38:52,360
Why this one? Why did I choose...

717
00:38:53,040 --> 00:38:54,120
This face?

718
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:56,360
CLARA: Doctor?
What's wrong with your face?

719
00:38:57,320 --> 00:38:58,680
I think I know why I chose it.

720
00:39:00,040 --> 00:39:01,320
It's like I'm trying
to tell myself something.

721
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:04,320
I think I know what I'm trying to say.

722
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:07,560
Just someone,
not the whole town.

723
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:10,360
Just save someone.

724
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:13,480
Come with me...

725
00:39:16,040 --> 00:39:18,920
I know where I got this face
and I know what it is for.

726
00:39:19,560 --> 00:39:20,600
Okay, what's it for?

727
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:25,320
To remind me,
to hold me to the mark.

728
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:29,560
I'm the Doctor, and I save people.

729
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:32,000
And if anyone happens to be listening,

730
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:34,440
anyone have a kind of
a problem with that,

731
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:37,000
to hell with you!

732
00:39:39,480 --> 00:39:40,520
(GRUNTS)

733
00:39:45,160 --> 00:39:46,440
What's he doing?

734
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:49,080
Saving her, I think.

735
00:39:49,160 --> 00:39:50,640
(WHOOSHING)

736
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:56,760
It's from the Mire helmet,
battlefield medical kit.

737
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:59,240
I've reprogrammed it for human beings.

738
00:40:08,560 --> 00:40:10,920
It's gone. It's inside her.

739
00:40:11,400 --> 00:40:12,920
It's repairing her.

740
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:15,560
It won't ever stop repairing her,
if it works.

741
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:17,320
Come on, Ashildr.

742
00:40:17,640 --> 00:40:20,240
Come on. The story's not over yet.

743
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:24,680
Daughter...

744
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:27,720
(SNIFFLES) Listen to me.

745
00:40:28,360 --> 00:40:31,000
This town has lost so much.

746
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:34,760
If we lose you, too,

747
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:37,800
there'll be nothing left.

748
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:55,400
(GASPS)

749
00:40:58,360 --> 00:40:59,480
-(WHEEZING)
-Ashildr.

750
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:02,640
She'll be conscious in a day.

751
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,880
Up and about in three.
No swimming for a week.

752
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:08,360
Now, we going to need a long boat
and some of your best rowers.

753
00:41:08,680 --> 00:41:10,800
We're two days sail from the TARDIS.
Come on, Clara!

754
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:12,840
No, wait, no.
She'll want to see you when she wakes.

755
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:16,440
Oh, no. Well, she'll see me
often enough once she understands.

756
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:17,800
Understands what?

757
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:21,000
Second dose.

758
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:23,720
-When she needs to take this?
-No, no, no.

759
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:24,840
It's not for her.

760
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:27,560
-Then who is it for?
-Ah, whoever she wants.

761
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:29,960
ASHILDR: Doctor...

762
00:41:31,440 --> 00:41:33,360
-Thank you.
-DOCTOR: Ah...

763
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:36,360
Don't thank me yet, Ashildr.

764
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:38,760
Not yet.

765
00:41:59,320 --> 00:42:00,560
CLARA: Okay, it's official.

766
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:02,800
Silence is even worse
in a Scottish accent.

767
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:04,680
Are you going to tell me
what you are brooding about?

768
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:06,040
It won't stop.

769
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:09,240
The repair kit I put inside of Ashildr,
long ago...

770
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:12,200
-It will just keep fixing her.
-Well, good.

771
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:14,640
I'm not sure,
but it is entirely possible

772
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:17,240
she has lost the ability to die.

773
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:20,840
-The ability?
-Oh! (CHUCKLES)

774
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:23,240
Dying is an ability, believe me.

775
00:42:24,840 --> 00:42:28,640
Barring accidents, she may
now be functionally immortal.

776
00:42:28,720 --> 00:42:30,320
(DOOR UNLOCKING)

777
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:33,640
If the repair kit
never stops working, then...

778
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:36,120
Why did you give her two?

779
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:40,360
Immortality isn't living forever,
that's not what it feels like.

780
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:44,400
Immortality is everybody else dying.

781
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:48,680
She might meet someone
she can't bear to lose.

782
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:54,320
That happens.

783
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:56,080
I believe.

784
00:43:01,240 --> 00:43:03,720
-(MACHINE INITIALISING)
-I was angry.

785
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:06,040
I was emotional.

786
00:43:06,360 --> 00:43:08,760
Just possibly,
I've made a terrible mistake.

787
00:43:10,920 --> 00:43:13,000
Maybe even a tidal wave.

788
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:20,720
Time will tell, it always does.

789
00:43:21,480 --> 00:43:23,880
CLARA: Whatever you did for Ashildr,

790
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:26,040
I think she deserved it.

791
00:43:26,960 --> 00:43:29,920
Yes. Yes, she did.

792
00:43:31,600 --> 00:43:33,720
But Ashildr isn't just human any more,

793
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:36,320
there's a little piece of alien
inside her.

794
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:38,080
So in a way, she's...

795
00:43:41,480 --> 00:43:42,800
In a way...

796
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:47,120
She is a hybrid.

797
00:45:12,600 --> 00:45:13,760
-(HORSE NEIGHING)
-Whoa!

798
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:15,400
-KNIGHTMARE: Stand and deliver.
-(SCREAMING)

799
00:45:16,240 --> 00:45:17,640
If I didn't know better,
I'd say this was a robbery.

800
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:19,160
The most wanted in the land.

801
00:45:19,240 --> 00:45:21,040
Now is not time to be showing off.

802
00:45:21,160 --> 00:45:23,400
GIRL: Could it be we are looking
for the same prize?

803
00:45:23,480 --> 00:45:25,000
The eyes of Hades.

804
00:45:25,080 --> 00:45:26,800
Who is this? Your sidekick?

805
00:45:26,880 --> 00:45:27,960
I'm not a sidekick.

806
00:45:28,040 --> 00:45:29,720
GIRL: Come on, sidekick watch me run.

807
00:45:29,800 --> 00:45:31,880
MR FANSHAWE:
There is an intruder on the premises!

808
00:45:31,960 --> 00:45:33,760
-What're you doing?
-It's kill or be killed.

809
00:45:33,840 --> 00:45:35,400
DOCTOR: You're playing with fire!

810
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:37,480
Do you have a cat?

